# Data Validation Rules

## Pandera invariants
- D-14 `Check.in_range(lo,hi)` derives from `eda/artifacts/01_dtypes_map.json`
- Nullable explicit (`nullable=True`), strict mode ON for prod inputs
- Schemas in `src/{service}/schemas.py` — single source of truth

## DVC
- `data/raw/`, `data/processed/` DVC-tracked + gitignored
- D-15 `eda/artifacts/02_baseline_distributions.pkl` DVC-tracked (drift input)
- Remotes: GCS (primary) + S3 (secondary)

## Lifecycle
EDA phase 6 → `schema_proposal.py` → human review → merge into `schemas.py`.
`test_schema_matches_eda.py` keeps ranges in sync. Never auto-overwrite.

## Forbidden
- Hardcoded ranges (`Check.in_range(0, 100)`) — derive from EDA
- Silent column drop — always raise or log

See AGENTS.md D-14/D-15, `.windsurf/rules/08-data-validation.md`, ADR-004.
